text: Sumter County is a county in the center of the U.S. state of Georgia. As of the 2020 census, the population was 29,616. The county seat is Americus. The county was created on December 26, 1831. ==References== Category:1830s establishments in Georgia (U.S. state) Category:1831 establishments in the United States Category:Georgia (U.S. state) counties
